~ chapter3_star_fragment

Player: Another Star Fragment...
Player: Your light... feels familiar.

Star Fragment: It is because you have brought my brothers and sisters home.

Star Fragment: Our light grows stronger with every Star Fragment you recover.

Player: Then...
Player: Are your memories returning?

Star Fragment: Little by little.

Star Fragment: Some memories remain beyond our reach...
Star Fragment: but I remember what this guardian once was.

Player: The Rebulto...

Star Fragment: Once, people came before it
Star Fragment: not to ask for miracles...

Star Fragment: ...but to find the strength to face tomorrow.

Star Fragment: It stood as a reminder
Star Fragment: that even in life's darkest moments,
Star Fragment: hope would always remain.

Player: And they turned it into a weapon.

Star Fragment: Yes.

Star Fragment: They knew that hope cannot be stolen by force.

Star Fragment: So they chose to corrupt it instead.

Star Fragment: If the people could no longer trust
Star Fragment: the very symbols that gave them hope...

Star Fragment: then despair would take root on its own.

Player: That's why every village we pass...

Player: ...feels so empty.

Star Fragment: Hope is a fragile flame, Blessed One.

Star Fragment: It need not be extinguished.

Star Fragment: People need only believe
Star Fragment: that it has already gone out.

Player: Then I'll become the proof that it still burns.

Star Fragment: Just as I remembered...

Star Fragment: You truly are the Blessed One.

Star Fragment: More of our memories are returning.

Star Fragment: Soon...

Star Fragment: We may finally remember
Star Fragment: the one who imprisoned the Stars.

Player: Then we'll find them.

Player: Together.

Star Fragment: I shall gladly walk beside you.

Star Fragment: I am Pag-asa,
Star Fragment: the Star of Hope.

Star Fragment: Carry hope within your heart...

Star Fragment: For it is the one light
Star Fragment: that even darkness cannot imitate.

=> END